    Abstract implementation of a context invocation factory.

    This class implements equals() and hashCode() methods employing the arguments specified in the constructor. Note, however, based on the specific object implementation the equality check may unexpectedly fail. For example, in case of a collection of arrays, the object will not be equal to another collection containing different arrays storing the same data. In fact an array equals() implementation does not override the Object one.
